### set up anaconda

[https://www.digitalocean.com/community/tutorials/how-to-install-anaconda-on-ubuntu-18-04-quickstart](link to set up anaconda)

Jetbain python has built in intergration with anaconda.  So create a project as a conda project.  This will create a virtual environment with the name of the project as the environment..

```bash
## install's tensorflow-gpu
conda install tensorflow-gpu 
## install pip in the conda envirment
conda install pip
## know you can use pip as a local install of packages


```
